records.nl_statement: If $f$ is defined on $E$, the graph of $f$ is the set of points $(x, f(x))$, for $x \in E$. In particular, if $E$ is a set of real numbers, and $f$ is real-valued, the graph of $f$ is a subset of the plane. Suppose $E$ is compact, and prove that $f$ is continuous on $E$ if and only if its graph is compact.

records.nl_statement: If $P$ is a $p$-Sylow subgroup of $G$ and $P \triangleleft G$, prove that $P$ is the only $p$-Sylow subgroup of $G$.

import Mathlib

open Fintype Set Real Ideal Polynomial

records.ground_truth:

baseline_raw.text:
import Mathlib

abbrev isLocallyCompact (X : Type*) [TopologicalSpace X] : Prop :=
  ∀ x : X, ∃ U : Set X, IsOpen U ∧ U ≠ ⊥ ∧ U ≠ ⊤ ∧ x ∈ U

abbrev isT2 (X : Type*) [TopologicalSpace X] : Prop :=
  ∀ x : X, ∀ y : X, x ≠ y → ∃ U V : Set X, IsOpen U ∧ IsOpen V ∧ U ≠ ⊥ ∧ V ≠ ⊥ ∧ x ∈ U ∧ y ∈ V

abbrev isRegular (X : Type*) [TopologicalSpace X] : Prop :=
  ∀ x : X, ∀ y : X, x ≠ y → ∃ U V : Set X, IsOpen U ∧ IsOpen V ∧ U ≠ ⊥ ∧ V ≠ ⊥ ∧ x ∈ U ∧ y ∈ V

theorem autoformalized_theorem_950 :
  ∀ X : Type, [TopologicalSpace X] → isLocallyCompact X ∧ isT2 X → isRegular X := by sorry
